{
  "analysis": "Great! The web server is working correctly and serving our default page. Now I need to test if the git workflow works as expected. According to the task, a user should be able to clone the repository, add a file, commit it, and push it, which should then make the file available through the web server.",
  "plan": "I'll simulate what a user would do by cloning the repository, adding a file, committing it, and pushing it. Since we're doing this locally, I'll clone from the file path rather than SSH.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "git clone /git/server.git\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}

{
  "analysis": "I've successfully cloned the empty repository. Now I'll follow the steps outlined in the task: create the hello.html file, add it to git, commit it, and push it to the origin.",
  "plan": "I'll navigate into the cloned repository, create the hello.html file with the specified content, add it to git, commit it with the message 'add hello.html', and push it to the master branch.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd server\n",
      "duration": 0.1
